// Memory mode for XLA:GPU collective operations.
//
// COLLECTIVES_PRIVATE_MEMORY:
//
//	Collective operations working on private device memory that lives in a
//	per-device memory space. This is also called two-sided collectives
//	because it requires both sides of the collective operation to exchange
//	local device pointers before they can make progress.
//
// COLLECTIVES_SYMMETRIC_MEMORY:
//
//	Collective operations working on symmetric device memory, which gives
//	a global view of device memory across all participating ranks. With
//	symmetric memory, collective operations can be implemented as one-sided
